---
import ChapterLayout from "../layouts/ChapterLayout.astro";
import ProjectCard from "../components/ProjectCard.astro";
import Divider from "../components/Divider.astro";
---

<ChapterLayout title="Projects" chapter="Chapter III">
  <p class="drop-cap text-charcoal/80 leading-relaxed mb-10">
    Here are some projects that I've worked on over the years. For the record, these projects were all completed before the generative AI era.
  </p>

  <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
    <ProjectCard
      title="Cronus"
      description="A reinforcement learning bot for Rocket League, trained to compete in aerial mechanics, positioning, and game sense through self-play."
      tags={["Python", "Reinforcement Learning"]}
      href="https://github.com/devynfisher10/Cronus"
    />
    <ProjectCard
      title="Europa"
      description="An earlier-generation Rocket League RL bot exploring different reward shaping and training strategies for competitive play."
      tags={["Python", "Reinforcement Learning"]}
      href="https://github.com/devynfisher10/Europa"
    />
    <ProjectCard
      title="Show Engine"
      description="Uses Universal Sentence Encoder to compute similarity scores between 1,000+ TV shows based on IMDB ratings, descriptions, and other features. Deployed with Streamlit."
      tags={["Python", "TensorFlow", "NLP", "Streamlit"]}
      href="https://github.com/devynfisher10/Show-Engine"
    />
    <ProjectCard
      title="Playlist Generator"
      description="Automatically generates collaborative playlists between friend groups by analyzing each user's existing Spotify playlists to determine shared song interest."
      tags={["JavaScript", "Spotify API"]}
      href="https://github.com/devynfisher10/playlist-generator"
    />
  </div>

  <Divider class="mt-10" />

  <p class="text-center text-charcoal/50 font-heading italic text-sm mt-4">
    Check <a href="https://github.com/devynfisher10" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="underline hover:text-burgundy transition-colors">GitHub</a> for the details.
  </p>
</ChapterLayout>
